CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 1, 1974, pg. 22, reads: "Dedicated To An Urgent Need - Are, from left to right: Alfred Morris, conductor of the Harper Symphony Orchestra, in Binghampton, N.Y. and former NEED recipient; John K. Tabor, Undersecretary of Commerce in Nixon Administration and principal speaker at the banquet; Naomi Sims, a New York fashion model and former NEED recipient, and Herman Reed [Reid], Executive Director of NEED (Harris Photo)."
TitMainTitle: John K. Tabor, Naomi Sims, and Alfred Morris standing at podium, possibly in Hilton Hotel, for NEED banquet
